
This is an future port of clMAGMA by Prof Jinchuan Tang (jctang@gzu.edu.cn). 
It supports many OpenCL 1.2+ devices and tuned clBLAST.
My students from GZU and myself are also active in tuning the clBLAST with many merged results in clBLAST. 
There maybe some Chinese comments in the code, use large language model to translate them to your own language if you need.
LLM may be used to improve the code due to lack of personals and funding on make them work.
I am also active in maintaining a sparse library called AnySparse porting from clSPARSE and most importantly AnyArray (formerly Octave ocl extra) for GNU Octave with gpuArray functionalities.

Routines are included for the following algorithms:

    * LU, QR, and Cholesky factorizations, with multi-GPU support
    * Hessenberg, bidiagonal, and tridiagonal reductions
    * Linear solvers based on LU, QR, and Cholesky
    * Eigenvalue and singular value problem solvers
    * Orthogonal transformation routines.

Most routines have all four precisions:
single (s), double (d), single-complex (c), double-complex (z).

